remarks: Given the equivalences set in the hypotheses, there exist a proof where ch, th, ta, et match ze, si accordingly (Contributed by Jarvin Udandy, 7-Sep-2016.)
statement:
mdandyvr14.1 $e |- ( ph <-> ze ) $.
mdandyvr14.2 $e |- ( ps <-> si ) $.
mdandyvr14.3 $e |- ( ch <-> ph ) $.
mdandyvr14.4 $e |- ( th <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvr14.5 $e |- ( ta <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvr14.6 $e |- ( et <-> ps ) $.
mdandyvr14 $p |- ( ( ( ( ch <-> ze ) /\ ( th <-> si ) ) /\ ( ta <-> si ) ) /\ ( et <-> si ) ) $.
